13:59.840 --> 14:01.005
Yes, sir.

14:01.007 --> 14:02.507
I'm on it, sir.

14:02.509 --> 14:06.311
Good.
Do not let me down.

14:14.119 --> 14:16.921
[ sighs ]

14:20.359 --> 14:21.893
Jake: I wouldn't.

14:21.895 --> 14:24.095
Crowds -- you don't want
to cause a scene.

14:24.097 --> 14:26.130
And I'm not here
to kill you,

14:26.132 --> 14:29.334
But from the looks
of your conversation with rowan,

14:29.336 --> 14:31.135
That'd probably be
my best move.

14:31.137 --> 14:33.171
You know, kill you
before you kill me.

14:33.173 --> 14:34.606
Orders.

14:34.608 --> 14:35.940
Right.

14:35.942 --> 14:37.642
Orders.

14:37.644 --> 14:39.944
But what happens
after I'm out of the way?

14:39.946 --> 14:41.312
You think rowan
lets the only other person

14:41.314 --> 14:43.181
Who can link him to the death
of the president's kid

14:43.183 --> 14:45.483
Walk around free
to tell tales?

14:50.322 --> 14:51.956
That's what this is about?

14:51.958 --> 14:53.391
He's covering
his ass, tom.

14:53.393 --> 14:54.492
I'm first.

14:54.494 --> 14:55.894
You're second.

14:55.896 --> 14:59.264
Well, you can't protect me
from him.

14:59.266 --> 15:00.331
I can try.

15:03.269 --> 15:05.570
Listen...
You may not trust me,

15:05.572 --> 15:08.072
But you know
you can't trust him.

15:11.977 --> 15:15.947
Well, if you do try to kill me,
maybe not today.

15:15.949 --> 15:18.049
It's gorgeous out.

15:24.089 --> 15:27.659
[ indistinct talking,
door opens ]

15:27.661 --> 15:30.128
Let's take a break.

15:34.033 --> 15:35.667
What do you have?

15:35.669 --> 15:38.136
Karen was only able to identify
one of the boys in the video,

15:38.138 --> 15:39.137
But my team is on him.

15:39.139 --> 15:40.405
We'll find the other one.

15:40.407 --> 15:42.607
It's just a matter of time.
We'll get him.

15:44.511 --> 15:47.946
I thought sending her back
to boarding school right away

15:47.948 --> 15:49.547
Was the best thing.

15:49.549 --> 15:52.016
Get her back to normal
as soon as possible,

15:52.018 --> 15:54.485
Dig in, have a routine,
back to work.

15:54.487 --> 15:56.955
I thought
it would help.

15:58.023 --> 16:01.225
Burying yourself in work
isn't always the best thing

16:01.227 --> 16:04.062
When you lose someone.

16:04.064 --> 16:07.098
Running away isn't always
the best thing, either.

16:16.742 --> 16:21.279
Liv...

16:21.281 --> 16:24.615
Where did you go?

16:28.120 --> 16:29.220
Fitz --

16:29.222 --> 16:30.488
Where did you go?

16:33.225 --> 16:38.329
You just...Took off
for two months, all alone?

16:43.102 --> 16:45.770
I...

16:46.739 --> 16:49.440
Yes.

16:49.442 --> 16:51.209
I did.

16:53.245 --> 16:55.747
I needed
some time alone.

16:55.749 --> 17:01.285
After everything,
I just needed to be alone.

17:01.287 --> 17:03.621
You were having
a difficult time.

17:06.058 --> 17:07.792
We were all having
a difficult time.

17:07.794 --> 17:10.328
I'm sorry.

17:11.263 --> 17:12.430
About your mother.

17:12.432 --> 17:13.498
No.

17:14.800 --> 17:16.100
She did
a terrible thing.

17:16.102 --> 17:17.101
Don't apologize.

17:17.103 --> 17:19.670
She ruined your family.

17:19.672 --> 17:21.606
She ruined my family.

17:25.778 --> 17:29.781
She ruined us.

17:42.294 --> 17:45.797
[ door opens, closes ]

17:48.767 --> 17:50.435
<i>You fought your way</i>
<i>through a very difficult</i>

17:50.437 --> 17:52.470
<i>Confirmation process</i>
<i>as a democrat.</i>

17:52.472 --> 17:54.672
<i>You delivered the president</i>
<i>his gun-control bill.</i>

17:54.674 --> 17:56.441
<i>Senators from both sides</i>
<i>of the aisle</i>

17:56.443 --> 17:58.376
<i>Seem to be bowing down</i>
<i>before you.</i>

17:58.378 --> 18:00.445
<i>So, attorney general rosen,</i>
<i>I have to ask --</i>

18:00.447 --> 18:02.080
<i>What's your secret?</i>

18:02.082 --> 18:03.614
<i>You know, ashley,</i>
<i>if I have a talent,</i>

18:03.616 --> 18:05.149
<i>It's that I'm able</i>
<i>to convince people</i>

18:05.151 --> 18:06.751
Which side of the argument
<i>they need to be on.</i>

18:06.753 --> 18:07.752
<i>Secrets?</i>

18:07.754 --> 18:09.620
I don't really have any.

18:09.622 --> 18:11.222
Rosen.

18:11.224 --> 18:12.323
Oh, hi.

18:12.325 --> 18:13.825
Am I due
for a good threatening?

18:13.827 --> 18:15.593
Funny, but I don't have time
for jokes.

18:15.595 --> 18:16.727
Rowan is trying
to kill me.

18:16.729 --> 18:18.229
So, I need your help.

18:18.231 --> 18:20.098
I need to know that
should anything happen to me,

18:20.100 --> 18:21.632
You'll release
the b613 files.

18:24.303 --> 18:25.670
No.

18:25.672 --> 18:28.306
I don't want anything more to do
with those files.

18:28.308 --> 18:30.241
I've got enough blood
on my hands already.

18:30.243 --> 18:31.742
I wish you'd never
given them to me.

18:31.744 --> 18:33.845
I wish
I'd never opened them.

18:33.847 --> 18:35.646
Then give them back
to me.

18:38.484 --> 18:39.884
No.

18:39.886 --> 18:41.752
Are you kidding me?

18:41.754 --> 18:43.754
Those files would bring down
the u.S. Government,

18:43.756 --> 18:45.490
Destroy over two centuries
of law and order

18:45.492 --> 18:48.159
And the world's
greatest democracy

18:48.161 --> 18:49.560
Would swirl down
the drain.

18:49.562 --> 18:52.897
No one should have them.
They shouldn't exist.

18:56.401 --> 19:00.138
Your morality means nothing,
not to me,

19:00.140 --> 19:03.207
Not to b613,
and certainly not to command.

19:03.209 --> 19:04.609
Give me the files

19:04.611 --> 19:07.445
Or I will snap your neck
right now.

19:18.457 --> 19:20.224
Here.

19:20.226 --> 19:21.826
Now get out.

19:21.828 --> 19:24.829
Thanks, rosen.

19:26.798 --> 19:30.401
[ <i>camera shutter clicking</i> ]

19:30.403 --> 19:32.537
[ cellphone rings ]

19:32.539 --> 19:33.538
Jake.

19:33.540 --> 19:34.739
I need to see you.
I'm busy.

19:34.741 --> 19:35.740
Well, this is important.

19:35.742 --> 19:38.242
Not really. There's something
I need to tell you.

19:38.244 --> 19:39.577
In person.

19:39.579 --> 19:41.779
I'm sorry, jake.
Olivia?

19:41.781 --> 19:44.282
I'm gonna need
to call you back.

19:45.317 --> 19:48.653
Olivia!

19:48.655 --> 19:50.721
Olivia!
Mellie.

19:50.723 --> 19:53.224
What are you doing here?

19:53.226 --> 19:55.693
I think that you should
discuss that with your husband.

19:55.695 --> 19:57.528
No.
What are you doing here?

19:57.530 --> 19:58.729
What are you doing
in my house?

19:58.731 --> 20:01.299
You tell me.
You tell me now.

20:08.774 --> 20:10.808
I've got secret service
ripping up the carpet

20:10.810 --> 20:15.580
In the past six months
that's not being scrutinized.
[ door opens, closes ]

20:15.582 --> 20:18.282
Good. What about the two agents
who lost karen last night?

20:18.284 --> 20:20.985
They're already
packing their bags, sir.

20:20.987 --> 20:24.789
Got some new boots on there?
A new color?

20:24.791 --> 20:26.390
You said
you would warn me.

20:26.392 --> 20:28.993
About you seeing
olivia pope.

20:30.762 --> 20:31.929
I'll just...

20:31.931 --> 20:34.732
You've got olivia pope
in my house.

20:34.734 --> 20:36.867
Mellie --
why did you bring
olivia here?

20:36.869 --> 20:38.336
I didn't bring her here.

20:38.338 --> 20:40.638
[ laughing ] right.

20:40.640 --> 20:42.640
A magical fairy
granted your wish

20:42.642 --> 20:45.509
And, poof, olivia pope
appeared in the oval office.

20:45.511 --> 20:47.678
Mellie.
Or you made one of your
masturbating

20:47.680 --> 20:49.880
Late-night phone calls,
and she came running over.

20:49.882 --> 20:51.449
I didn't call olivia.

20:51.451 --> 20:52.750
Karen did.

20:52.752 --> 20:55.653
Karen got into some trouble
last night.

20:55.655 --> 20:57.922
There was a party,
she got drunk, things got...

20:59.558 --> 21:01.559
You should be glad
she called liv.

21:02.628 --> 21:03.628
I should be glad?

21:03.630 --> 21:04.895
Liv got her out of there.

21:04.897 --> 21:06.564
She's handling
the situation.

21:06.566 --> 21:07.598
I should be glad?!

21:07.600 --> 21:09.900
Mellie, focus.

21:09.902 --> 21:11.302
I am the mother.

21:11.304 --> 21:13.037
This is not <i>her</i> family.

21:13.039 --> 21:14.805
This is <i>my</i> family.

21:14.807 --> 21:16.407
I am the one
who picks up the pieces.

21:16.409 --> 21:17.742
I am the one
who holds this family together.

21:17.744 --> 21:19.010
I want her out of here.

21:19.012 --> 21:21.312
You get olivia pope
out of here.

21:21.314 --> 21:23.481
I don't want her
anywhere near my child.

21:23.483 --> 21:25.883
<i>I</i> will fix this.
<i>I</i> will make the decisions.

21:25.885 --> 21:27.952
You know what?
You just stay out it.

21:29.621 --> 21:31.656
I have dealt
with drunk mellie,

21:31.658 --> 21:33.658
Bad hygiene mellie --
no, wait.

21:33.660 --> 21:35.426
I got it --
smelly mellie.

21:35.428 --> 21:37.395
I have dealt
with drunk mellie

21:37.397 --> 21:38.796
And smelly mellie

21:38.798 --> 21:42.667
And "screw everything to hell"
mellie and crybaby mellie

21:42.669 --> 21:44.769
And "eat everything that is not
nailed down" mellie.

21:44.771 --> 21:48.739
But I will <i>not</i> put up
with whatever

21:48.741 --> 21:52.343
Righteous history-rewriting
mellie you have going on

21:52.345 --> 21:53.878
Right here, right now.

21:53.880 --> 21:55.446
This is not your family.

21:55.448 --> 21:58.349
You are not the mother,
not since jerry died.

21:58.351 --> 22:00.551
Since jerry died,
you have abdicated your role.

22:00.553 --> 22:01.819
You have mothered no one.

22:01.821 --> 22:04.855
You hold nothing together.
You pick up no pieces.

22:04.857 --> 22:06.324
You know how I know this?

22:06.326 --> 22:08.759
Because baby teddy
thinks his mother is nanny jen

22:08.761 --> 22:11.896
And karen spent last night
in a threesome with two guys

22:11.898 --> 22:14.932
They like to call
eiffel towering!

22:14.934 --> 22:16.867
You know how I know that?

22:16.869 --> 22:18.836
I saw the sex tape
they made!

22:18.838 --> 22:20.938
So you should be damn glad
she called olivia

22:20.940 --> 22:22.673
Because olivia pope
is fixing this mess,

22:22.675 --> 22:23.674
This mess that you made.

22:23.676 --> 22:26.010
This mess that <i>we</i> made.

22:26.012 --> 22:28.579
Look, I know that I share
some guilt in all of this.

22:28.581 --> 22:31.749
But you want to know the
difference between you and me?

22:31.751 --> 22:34.085
All day, every day,
I am running a country.

22:34.087 --> 22:36.554
I am grieving
for the loss of my son,

22:36.556 --> 22:39.457
But I am also running
a country.

22:39.459 --> 22:41.092
All day, every day,

22:41.094 --> 22:45.796
You are sitting around
in booties and a dirty robe

22:45.798 --> 22:49.967
Eating chips and getting drunk
at 11:00 a.M.!

22:55.841 --> 22:58.109
A sex tape?

23:01.980 --> 23:04.382
Yeah.

23:08.754 --> 23:12.022
She takes after her daddy, then,
doesn't she?

23:30.876 --> 23:31.942
[  <i>camera shutter clicking</i>]

23:35.046 --> 23:37.081
Where's the video,
bobby?

23:37.083 --> 23:38.783
Who the hell are you?

23:38.785 --> 23:40.818
I know who you are,
bobby.

23:40.820 --> 23:42.420
I know you're on full
scholarship at franklin prep.

23:42.422 --> 23:47.892
And you work this crappy
minimum-wage job at
gettysburger to help out.

23:47.894 --> 23:50.661
You're a hard worker --
a bootstrapper. I respect that.

23:50.663 --> 23:52.830
But you should know,
I will personally make sure

23:52.832 --> 23:55.800
You lose that scholarship
and this crappy minimum-wage job

23:55.802 --> 23:58.903
If you don't tell me
where you're keeping the video

23:58.905 --> 24:00.871
Of the girl
you and your buddy screwed

24:00.873 --> 24:02.106
At that party last night.

24:02.108 --> 24:03.874
I need answers, bobby.

24:03.876 --> 24:05.776
[ stammers, gasps ]

24:05.778 --> 24:07.912
[ <i>camera shutter clicking</i> ]

24:07.914 --> 24:10.214
Sorry I haven't had time
to talk,

24:10.216 --> 24:12.082
But I was thinking,
my place for dinner tonight?

24:12.084 --> 24:13.984
I'll cook.
Okay, I won't.

24:13.986 --> 24:17.521
But I'll get the finest takeout
d.C. Has to offer.

24:17.523 --> 24:18.856
Call me back.

24:18.858 --> 24:21.225
Or I'll just see you tonight.

24:21.227 --> 24:22.460
[ sighs ]

24:22.462 --> 24:23.594
They have this
four score promotion

24:23.596 --> 24:27.198
Buy four burgers
and get the fifth one free.

24:28.467 --> 24:29.567
Okay. Right.

24:29.569 --> 24:31.836
He coughed up the name
of his doubles partner,

24:31.838 --> 24:33.704
Donald "tripp" morgan iii.

24:33.706 --> 24:35.473
Only son -- thank god --
of margaret and donald jr.

24:35.475 --> 24:36.974
Are they local?
Bethesda.

24:36.976 --> 24:38.476
Let's bring them in.

24:40.479 --> 24:42.780
Mr. And mrs. Morgan,
thank you for coming in.

24:42.782 --> 24:44.748
Seems our son
has gotten himself into

24:44.750 --> 24:46.650
Another truly
unfortunate situation.

24:46.652 --> 24:48.919
[ chuckles ]
the understatement of the year.

24:48.921 --> 24:50.821
Honestly,
I'm at the end of my rope.

24:50.823 --> 24:52.857
Between the calls
from the st. Alban's headmaster

24:52.859 --> 24:54.658
Every other day
and now this,

24:54.660 --> 24:57.127
We just don't know
what we're gonna do with him.

24:57.129 --> 24:59.263
The boy's wild.
He always has been.

24:59.265 --> 25:02.166
Luckily, we've managed
to keep tripp's adventures

25:02.168 --> 25:03.767
Under the radar so far.

25:03.769 --> 25:05.202
I guess what those
college admissions officers

25:05.204 --> 25:07.872
Don't know
won't hurt them, right?

25:07.874 --> 25:10.107
I'm glad to hear
we're all on the same page.

25:10.109 --> 25:11.876
And that you understand
the consequences

25:11.878 --> 25:13.844
For not only your son,
but your entire family,

25:13.846 --> 25:16.013
Should a video like this
fall into the wrong hands.

25:16.015 --> 25:18.249
We are certainly aware
of the stakes here, ms. Pope.

25:18.251 --> 25:19.817
Good.

25:19.819 --> 25:23.220
Permanently delete the file
and its directory.

25:23.222 --> 25:25.823
We'll also run a scan on
your devices and cloud network

25:25.825 --> 25:27.925
To make sure
no trace of it remains.

25:29.794 --> 25:31.529
How much?

25:32.998 --> 25:34.865
I'm sorry?

25:34.867 --> 25:38.102
I mean, you want it,
you're gonna have to pay for it.

25:38.104 --> 25:40.671
We really have no idea
what the going rate

25:40.673 --> 25:43.040
For a sex tape starring
the first daughter is,

25:43.042 --> 25:44.875
But...

25:44.877 --> 25:46.610
We imagine
it's a hell of a lot.

25:48.914 --> 25:50.948
Fitz:
Say it again.

25:50.950 --> 25:51.949
The parents want money.

25:51.951 --> 25:53.918
$2.5 million?

25:53.920 --> 26:00.024
The president of [chuckling]
the United States of america?

26:01.860 --> 26:03.661
Come on, liv.

26:03.663 --> 26:05.563
You have the money.

26:05.565 --> 26:09.300
Do you want to refuse
to give it to them?

26:09.302 --> 26:12.336
But then they could
release the video.

26:12.338 --> 26:15.806
The video of your daughter
having sex with two boys.

26:15.808 --> 26:18.842
That video will become
karen's story.

26:18.844 --> 26:20.945
It will become who she is
for the rest of her life.

26:20.947 --> 26:23.714
She'll be no better
than a reality star,

26:23.716 --> 26:26.617
It will be
what they remember her for,

26:26.619 --> 26:28.719
Not her charity work,
not her accomplishments,

26:28.721 --> 26:30.854
Not her brain --
her sex tape.

26:30.856 --> 26:33.724
And I know that you want more
for your daughter.

26:33.726 --> 26:36.627
The most powerful man
in the world,

26:36.629 --> 26:37.995
An entire army
at my disposal,

26:37.997 --> 26:41.332
And I can't stop two idiots
from releasing a tape.

26:43.201 --> 26:45.669
Not in the world
of the internet.

26:46.705 --> 26:49.139
What kind of parents
are they?

26:49.141 --> 26:51.809
The world is full
of terrible parents.

26:51.811 --> 26:53.777
[ sighs ]

26:53.779 --> 26:55.879
I didn't mean you.

26:55.881 --> 26:56.914
Why not?

26:58.016 --> 26:59.383
I'm failing.

26:59.385 --> 27:01.952
Fitz.

27:01.954 --> 27:04.655
I'm a failure
as a father.

27:04.657 --> 27:08.892
And clearly, we can all agree
I'm a failure as a husband.

27:08.894 --> 27:11.128
Fitz.

27:16.201 --> 27:19.703
What, am I a failure
as a man, too?

27:21.273 --> 27:27.177
Don't ever leave me
like that again.

27:27.179 --> 27:29.413
I almost didn't survive.

27:29.415 --> 27:32.049
I almost died without you.

27:35.353 --> 27:37.821
Didn't you miss me?

27:37.823 --> 27:40.858
Liv.

27:40.860 --> 27:42.960
[ breathing heavily ]

27:49.067 --> 27:51.035
Didn't you miss me?

27:51.037 --> 27:53.737
Even a little?

27:58.109 --> 28:00.844
Oh, I did miss you.

28:08.687 --> 28:09.687
Stop.
No.

28:09.689 --> 28:10.688
I can't.

28:10.690 --> 28:11.855
Stop.
Why?

28:11.857 --> 28:12.856
Why not?

28:12.858 --> 28:14.925
Why can't you?

28:15.927 --> 28:17.795
What's the point?

28:19.330 --> 28:22.966
I didn't go away alone.

28:27.338 --> 28:29.039
You didn't go away alone.

28:29.041 --> 28:31.008
No.

28:34.345 --> 28:36.447
You went with jake.

28:36.449 --> 28:39.717
Yes.

28:41.820 --> 28:43.253
Say it.

28:43.255 --> 28:45.989
Fitz.

28:45.991 --> 28:47.891
Say it.

28:47.893 --> 28:49.059
[ sighs ]

28:49.061 --> 28:50.994
I went with jake.

28:59.304 --> 29:02.072
[ sighs ]

29:04.843 --> 29:09.847
So I <i>am</i> failing as a father
and a husband and a man.

29:09.849 --> 29:11.915
Good to know.

29:15.987 --> 29:20.924
Heavy is the head
that wears the crown, they say.

29:22.260 --> 29:23.961
Fitz, I know --

29:23.963 --> 29:25.796
Ow.

29:27.799 --> 29:31.335
Pay the morgans
the $2.5 million.

29:31.337 --> 29:34.037
[ ice rattles in glass,
liquid pours ]

29:34.039 --> 29:38.142
Do you want to discuss it
with mellie or...

29:40.912 --> 29:45.949
Because...My marriage
is such a partnership?

29:45.951 --> 29:47.851
I'm so happy?

29:48.920 --> 29:51.321
Pay the morgans
the $2.5 million.

29:51.323 --> 29:54.258
Let's just do
what my father would do.

29:54.260 --> 29:57.194
Throw money at the problem
and sweep it under the rug.

29:59.564 --> 30:03.000
[ door opens, closes ]

30:07.939 --> 30:10.407
$2.5 million, as promised.
I just need --

30:10.409 --> 30:11.909
You didn't tell her?
Tell me what?

30:11.911 --> 30:13.510
Uh, we're gonna need
another $500,000.

30:13.512 --> 30:15.479
To cover expenses.

30:15.481 --> 30:16.947
